1444
01:03:20,620 --> 01:03:22,120
and it's nice to say they go

1445
01:03:22,120 --> 01:03:23,620
from zero to two pi, that's all.

1446
01:03:23,620 --> 01:03:27,620
But they go from zero to pi.

1447
01:03:27,620 --> 01:03:30,120
So this sum over the mass

1448
01:03:30,120 --> 01:03:32,620
points is going to be an integral

1449
01:03:32,620 --> 01:03:34,620
from zero to pi, d sigma.

1450
01:03:34,620 --> 01:03:35,620
This is adding up.

1451
01:03:35,620 --> 01:03:36,620
This is adding up.

1452
01:03:36,620 --> 01:03:38,620
This is adding them all up.

1453
01:03:38,620 --> 01:03:41,620
And we're going to have the kinetic energy

1454
01:03:41,620 --> 01:03:49,620
of the little element of string at point sigma.

1455
01:03:49,620 --> 01:03:51,620
We have a continuous string now.

1456
01:03:51,620 --> 01:03:54,620
We take a little element at point sigma.

1457
01:03:54,620 --> 01:03:58,620
We take its velocity squared and divide by two.

1458
01:03:58,620 --> 01:04:02,620
And what about this term over here?

1459
01:04:02,620 --> 01:04:05,620
I've chosen the mass to go

1460
01:04:05,620 --> 01:04:09,620
in the appropriate way of dropping the mass here.

1461
