01:06:58,620 --> 01:07:01,620
as to make this...

1526
01:07:01,620 --> 01:07:05,620
And this is the conventional energy of a vibrating string.

1527
01:07:05,620 --> 01:07:09,620
It has two terms, kinetic and potential.

1528
01:07:09,620 --> 01:07:11,620
Potential proportional to the stretching.

1529
01:07:11,620 --> 01:07:14,120
This is the x d sigma

1530
01:07:14,120 --> 01:07:16,620
is the stretching of the string.

1531
01:07:16,620 --> 01:07:21,620
Okay, I want to point out one interesting fact.

1532
01:07:21,620 --> 01:07:25,620
This Hamiltonian here,

1533
01:07:25,620 --> 01:07:27,620
or this expression for energy,

1534
01:07:27,620 --> 01:07:32,620
is the generalization of this expression here

1535
01:07:32,620 --> 01:07:35,620
for a system of particles

1536
01:07:35,620 --> 01:07:38,620
which also has an interaction between them.

1537
01:07:38,620 --> 01:07:42,620
But the whole thing, the whole object,

1538
01:07:42,620 --> 01:07:45,620
it may be vibrating and doing things,

1539
01:07:45,620 --> 01:07:47,620
but the whole object is an object.

1540
01:07:47,620 --> 01:07:49,620
We can call it a particle.

1541
01:07:49,620 --> 01:07:51,620
Who's to say it's not a particle?

1542
01:07:54,620 --> 01:07:56,620
Protons and neutrons have spin.

1543
01:07:56,620 --> 01:07:57,620
They rotate.

1544
01:07:57,620 --> 01:08:00,620
There's all sorts of internal motions in particles.

1545
01:08:00,620 --> 01:08:03,620
We know there are internal motions of particles,

1546
01:08:03,620 --> 01:08:05,620
internal motions of atoms,

1547
01:08:05,620 --> 01:08:09,620
internal motions of quarks inside protons and neutrons.

1548
01:08:09,620 --> 01:08:11,620
The best bet would be there

1549
01:08:11,620 --> 01:08:13,620
are all sorts of internal motions

1550
01:08:13,620 --> 01:08:15,620
in every particle.

1551
01:08:15,620 --> 01:08:17,620
So this stringy vibrations and

1552
01:08:17,620 --> 01:08:19,620
internal motions and so forth,

1553
01:08:19,620 --> 01:08:22,620
that perhaps, not perhaps,

1554
01:08:22,620 --> 01:08:24,620
but would add up to all

1555
01:08:24,620 --> 01:08:26,620
the internal motion in the particle.

1556
01:08:26,620 --> 01:08:29,620
All the internal energy in the particle.

1557
01:08:29,620 --> 01:08:34,620
The internal energy would be the contributions to the energy

1558
01:08:34,620 --> 01:08:37,620
from the potential stretching

1559
01:08:37,620 --> 01:08:41,620
and from the relative motion of the different parts.

1560
01:08:41,620 --> 01:08:43,620
The overall motion,

1561
01:08:43,620 --> 01:08:45,620
we'll separate that out soon enough,

1562
01:08:45,620 --> 01:08:47,620
but the overall motion of the string,

1563
01:08:47,620 --> 01:08:49,620
the center of mass of it,

1564
01:08:49,620 --> 01:08:51,620
that would just be treated

1565
01:08:51,620 --> 01:08:53,620
as the position of the particle.

1566
01:08:53,620 --> 01:08:55,620
But the relative stretching

1567
01:08:55,620 --> 01:08:57,620
and the relative vibration,

1568
01:08:57,620 --> 01:08:59,620
that's internal energy.

1569
01:08:59,620 --> 01:09:03,620
So, when we calculate the internal energy of this particle,

1570
01:09:03,620 --> 01:09:05,620
what should we relate it to?

1571
01:09:05,620 --> 01:09:08,620
We should relate it not to the mass,

1572
01:09:08,620 --> 01:09:11,620
but to the mass squared.

1573
01:09:13,620 --> 01:09:16,620
In this correspondence,

1574
01:09:16,620 --> 01:09:17,620
it's not an analogy,

1575
01:09:17,620 --> 01:09:23,620
it's an exact statement about the properties of relativity.

1576
01:09:23,620 --> 01:09:25,620
It's a very precise statement.

1577
01:09:25,620 --> 01:09:27,620
It's a very precise mathematical statement,

1578
01:09:27,620 --> 01:09:28,620
which I won't make now,

1579
01:09:28,620 --> 01:09:30,620
but there is an exact sense

1580
01:09:30,620 --> 01:09:32,620
in which fast-moving systems

1581
01:09:32,620 --> 01:09:35,620
are completely non-relativistic

1582
01:09:35,620 --> 01:09:37,620
in the two-dimensional sense.

1583
01:09:37,620 --> 01:09:41,620
What would the internal energy correspond to?

1584
01:09:41,620 --> 01:09:44,620
It would correspond not to the mass of the particle,

1585
01:09:44,620 --> 01:09:47,620
but to the mass squared.

1586
01:09:47,620 --> 01:09:50,620
So, for a string at rest,

1587
01:09:50,620 --> 01:09:53,620
think of a string which has no motion

1588
01:09:53,620 --> 01:09:55,620
in the x-axis,

1589
01:09:55,620 --> 01:09:57,620
but is in a x-y plane.

1590
01:09:57,620 --> 01:09:59,620
All it's doing is vibrating,

1591
01:09:59,620 --> 01:10:01,620
and it has internal energy.

1592
01:10:01,620 --> 01:10:04,620
That internal energy has to be identified

1593
01:10:04,620 --> 01:10:06,620
with the square of the mass

1594
01:10:06,620 --> 01:10:11,620
of the entire assembly of constituents of the string.

1595
01:10:11,620 --> 01:10:13,620
If the constituents of the string

1596
01:10:13,620 --> 01:10:15,620
are adding up to something

1597
01:10:15,620 --> 01:10:18,620
that we want to call a particle,

1598
01:10:18,620 --> 01:10:21,620
then that particle has a mass squared,

1599
01:10:21,620 --> 01:10:25,620
which is the sum of all of the internal energies

1600
01:10:25,620 --> 01:10:26,620
of the particle.

1601
01:10:26,620 --> 01:10:28,620
Now, this is an interesting fact.

1602
01:10:28,620 --> 01:10:31,620
We get mass squared

1603
01:10:31,620 --> 01:10:33,620
for the energy of a particle

1604
01:10:33,620 --> 01:10:35,620
in this framework.

1605
01:10:43,620 --> 01:10:45,620
There are some C's around,

1606
01:10:45,620 --> 01:10:47,620
which I haven't tried to keep track of.

1607
01:10:47,620 --> 01:10:49,620
There are C's,

1608
01:10:49,620 --> 01:10:51,620
and, yeah, there are C's,

1609
01:10:51,620 --> 01:10:53,620
and, right.

1610
01:10:53,620 --> 01:10:55,620
Yeah, I haven't tried to keep track of them.

1611
01:10:55,620 --> 01:10:57,620
But,

1612
01:11:01,620 --> 01:11:03,620
this connection was something I knew

1613
01:11:03,620 --> 01:11:05,620
that nobody else knew at the time.

1614
01:11:07,620 --> 01:11:09,620
I worked on both these things.

1615
01:11:09,620 --> 01:11:12,620
And, so,

1616
01:11:12,620 --> 01:11:14,620
this is interesting.

1617
01:11:14,620 --> 01:11:15,620
This is exciting.

1618
01:11:15,620 --> 01:11:16,620
Another fact.

1619
01:11:16,620 --> 01:11:20,620
Another fact is that a string

1620
01:11:20,620 --> 01:11:22,620
