01:21:52,620 --> 01:21:55,620
we conclude that if we were in the rest frame,

1900
01:21:55,620 --> 01:21:57,120
the energy of the string

1901
01:21:57,120 --> 01:21:58,620
would be proportional to its length.

1902
01:21:58,620 --> 01:22:00,620
And that's interesting,

1903
01:22:00,620 --> 01:22:03,620
because there's a wide variety of interesting

1904
01:22:03,620 --> 01:22:06,620
string-like objects that occur in field theory,

1905
01:22:06,620 --> 01:22:08,620
and they're called field theories,

1906
01:22:08,620 --> 01:22:10,620
not made out of atoms,

1907
01:22:10,620 --> 01:22:12,620
but made out of field configurations,

1908
01:22:12,620 --> 01:22:15,620
which have exactly the same property.

1909
01:22:22,620 --> 01:22:25,620
All right, let's come back in a few minutes.

1910
01:22:25,620 --> 01:22:30,620
I think I probably exhausted your attention for today.

1911
01:22:30,620 --> 01:22:32,620
But let me summarize.

1912
01:22:32,620 --> 01:22:34,620
Let me summarize.

1913
01:22:34,620 --> 01:22:36,620
Let me summarize.

1914
01:22:36,620 --> 01:22:38,620
Experimental properties of,

1915
01:22:38,620 --> 01:22:43,620
of hadrons indicated this kind of

1916
01:22:43,620 --> 01:22:46,620
excitations along a line.

1917
01:22:46,620 --> 01:22:49,620
Had we been smart at the time,

1918
01:22:49,620 --> 01:22:51,620
