1927
01:23:12,620 --> 01:23:17,620
That was the consequence of this relationship here.

1928
01:23:17,620 --> 01:23:19,620
All right, that was one fact.

1929
01:23:19,620 --> 01:23:21,620
Next fact.

1930
01:23:21,620 --> 01:23:23,620
Relativistic physics in a frame

1931
01:23:23,620 --> 01:23:25,620
in which everything is moving fast

1932
01:23:25,620 --> 01:23:28,620
is the same as non-relativistic physics,

1933
01:23:28,620 --> 01:23:31,620
except in one less dimension.

1934
01:23:31,620 --> 01:23:34,620
In one less dimension.

1935
01:23:34,620 --> 01:23:36,620
And so we can say that,

1936
01:23:36,620 --> 01:23:39,620
and so we can try to

1937
01:23:39,620 --> 01:23:42,620
build a simple theory of relativistic strings

1938
01:23:42,620 --> 01:23:44,620
by going to such a

1939
01:23:44,620 --> 01:23:46,620
frame and just using non-relativistic physics,

1940
01:23:46,620 --> 01:23:48,620
but in one less dimension.

1941
01:23:48,620 --> 01:23:49,620
Here it is.

1942
01:23:49,620 --> 01:23:53,620
Here's the non-relativistic string in two-dimensional space.

1943
01:23:53,620 --> 01:23:55,620
The only thing we have to remember

1944
01:23:55,620 --> 01:23:57,620
is that wherever we saw energy,

1945
01:23:57,620 --> 01:23:59,620
we have to think of

1946
01:23:59,620 --> 01:24:01,620
it, or internal energy in particular,

1947
01:24:01,620 --> 01:24:03,620
