and this way.

2170
01:34:07,620 --> 01:34:09,620
Now you cool it down

2171
01:34:09,620 --> 01:34:11,620
so that it becomes a superconductor

2172
01:34:11,620 --> 01:34:16,620
and you draw out the magnet.

2173
01:34:16,620 --> 01:34:18,620
These lines of flux here

2174
01:34:18,620 --> 01:34:20,620
will get pulled into the magnet.

2175
01:34:20,620 --> 01:34:23,620
Even after you've pulled out the magnet,

2176
01:34:23,620 --> 01:34:26,620
the lines of flux will go through that magnet

2177
01:34:26,620 --> 01:34:32,620
and they will form a thin tube through that magnet.

2178
01:34:32,620 --> 01:34:36,620
The field along the tube will be uniform.

2179
01:34:36,620 --> 01:34:38,620
And because the field is uniform,

2180
01:34:38,620 --> 01:34:41,620
that means the energy per unit length is fixed.

2181
01:34:41,620 --> 01:34:44,620
Okay, now, let's go a little bit further.

2182
01:34:44,620 --> 01:34:47,620
Imagine that we had magnetic monopoles.

2183
01:34:47,620 --> 01:34:49,620
We can actually simulate magnetic monopoles,

2184
01:34:49,620 --> 01:34:52,620
but let's suppose we really did have magnetic monopoles,

2185
01:34:52,620 --> 01:34:57,620
that there really were magnetic monopoles in the world.

2186
01:34:57,620 --> 01:34:59,620
And there may well be,

2187
01:34:59,620 --> 01:35:01,620
but we haven't discovered them yet.

2188
01:35:01,620 --> 01:35:03,620
But let's suppose we have discovered them

2189
01:35:03,620 --> 01:35:05,620
and we can manipulate them.

2190
01:35:05,620 --> 01:35:09,620
Okay, then we could take a monopole and an antimonopole,

2191
01:35:09,620 --> 01:35:11,620
put them right on top of each other,

2192
01:35:11,620 --> 01:35:16,620
don't let them annihilate, keep them a little bit apart.

2193
01:35:16,620 --> 01:35:18,620
Take them and put them into the superconductor.

2194
01:35:18,620 --> 01:35:22,620
Monopole and antimonopole.

2195
01:35:22,620 --> 01:35:24,620
I'm not going to tell you which one is which,

2196
01:35:24,620 --> 01:35:26,620
I'm just going to draw two of them.

2197
01:35:26,620 --> 01:35:29,620
And of course the monopole and the antimonopole

2198
01:35:29,620 --> 01:35:34,620
have some flux lines between them.

2199
01:35:34,620 --> 01:35:36,620
Now cool down the superconductor.

2200
01:35:36,620 --> 01:35:39,620
And take the monopole and the antimonopole

2201
01:35:39,620 --> 01:35:41,620
and start to separate them.

2202
01:35:41,620 --> 01:35:43,620
What happens?

2203
01:35:43,620 --> 01:35:45,620
Exactly the same thing that we think happens

2204
01:35:45,620 --> 01:35:47,620
between a pair of quarks.

2205
01:35:48,620 --> 01:35:52,620
Except that this is just an ordinary magnetic field

2206
01:35:52,620 --> 01:35:55,620
between the monopole and the antimonopole.

2207
01:35:55,620 --> 01:35:57,620
So inside a superconductor,

2208
01:35:57,620 --> 01:36:01,620
a monopole and an antimonopole would have an energy

2209
01:36:01,620 --> 01:36:04,620
which would be proportional to the distance between them.

2210
01:36:04,620 --> 01:36:06,620
Why the distance between them?

2211
01:36:06,620 --> 01:36:09,120
Because the string between them has

2212
01:36:09,120 --> 01:36:11,620
an energy proportional to its length.

2213
01:36:11,620 --> 01:36:13,620
Okay.

2214
01:36:13,620 --> 01:36:15,120
The monopole and the antimonopole

2215
01:36:15,120 --> 01:36:16,620
could not separate from each other,

2216
01:36:16,620 --> 01:36:17,620
they would be confined,

2217
01:36:17,620 --> 01:36:19,620
because as you start to separate them,

2218
01:36:19,620 --> 01:36:21,620
the energy goes up with the length,

2219
01:36:21,620 --> 01:36:31,620
and that's the character of what happens to hadrons,

2220
01:36:31,620 --> 01:36:33,620
or quarks in a hadron,

2221
01:36:33,620 --> 01:36:35,620
you separate them and their energy goes up.

2222
01:36:35,620 --> 01:36:37,620
So okay, so this is a system

2223
01:36:37,620 --> 01:36:40,620
where the energy is proportional to the length,

2224
01:36:40,620 --> 01:36:43,120
and it has the characteristics

2225
01:36:43,120 --> 01:36:45,620
of the same kind of string.

2226
01:36:45,620 --> 01:36:47,620
Does that answer your question?

2227
01:36:47,620 --> 01:36:49,620
Did you ever ask me?

2228
01:36:49,620 --> 01:36:51,620
I don't know who asked me.

2229
01:36:51,620 --> 01:36:53,620
Oh well, I guess he's gone.

2230
01:36:57,620 --> 01:36:59,620
The question was,

2231
01:36:59,620 --> 01:37:02,620
what's taking the role of the superfluid for the hadrons?

2232
01:37:02,620 --> 01:37:07,620
What is the superconducting fluid?

2233
01:37:07,620 --> 01:37:11,620
Virtual monopoles.

2234
01:37:11,620 --> 01:37:13,620
That's what it's thought to be, virtual monopoles,

2235
01:37:13,620 --> 01:37:15,620
but not these different monopoles.

2236
01:37:15,620 --> 01:37:22,620
These are called chromodynamic monopoles.

2237
01:37:22,620 --> 01:37:25,620
In the superconductor here,

2238
01:37:25,620 --> 01:37:28,620
the condensate, the superconducting condensate,

2239
01:37:28,620 --> 01:37:30,620
is made out of electric charge,

2240
01:37:30,620 --> 01:37:34,620
and it causes confinement of magnetic charge.

2241
01:37:34,620 --> 01:37:38,620
In quantum chromodynamics,

2242
01:37:38,620 --> 01:37:40,620
quarks are confined,

2243
01:37:40,620 --> 01:37:43,620
and they are kind of the electric charges

2244
01:37:43,620 --> 01:37:46,620
of quantum chromodynamics.

2245
01:37:46,620 --> 01:37:49,620
The things which condense are magnetic charges.

2246
01:37:49,620 --> 01:37:52,620
You say, where are those magnetic charges?

2247
01:37:52,620 --> 01:37:53,620
Why don't we see them?

2248
01:37:53,620 --> 01:37:56,620
Because they're always condensed in the vacuum.

2249
01:37:56,620 --> 01:37:59,620
But this is beyond what

2250
01:37:59,620 --> 01:38:02,620
I intended to talk about today.

2251
01:38:02,620 --> 01:38:06,620
Okay, what other questions come up?

2252
01:38:06,620 --> 01:38:08,620
Oh, it's almost 9 o'clock.

2253
01:38:08,620 --> 01:38:10,620
Okay, yeah.

2254
01:38:10,620 --> 01:38:11,620
So the energy being proportional to the length,

2255
01:38:11,620 --> 01:38:18,620
is the rule for highly relativistic string?

2256
01:38:18,620 --> 01:38:21,620
Well, a superconductor is not a highly relativistic,

2257
01:38:21,620 --> 01:38:22,620
it's a...

2258
01:38:22,620 --> 01:38:24,620
It's also not a string.

2259
01:38:24,620 --> 01:38:26,620
No, no, but it's string-like.

2260
01:38:26,620 --> 01:38:30,620
So if you took a regular Hooke's law,

2261
01:38:30,620 --> 01:38:32,620
string made of springs,

2262
01:38:32,620 --> 01:38:35,620
and had it going relativistically inside,

2263
01:38:35,620 --> 01:38:38,620
Assuming you could...

2264
01:38:38,620 --> 01:38:40,620
You'll have to make up some theory, I don't know.

2265
01:38:40,620 --> 01:38:42,620
You'll have to make up some theory.

2266
01:38:42,620 --> 01:38:45,120
But that construction would then have

2267
01:38:45,120 --> 01:38:47,620
an energy proportional to its length.

2268
01:38:47,620 --> 01:38:49,620
I don't know what it would do.

2269
01:38:49,620 --> 01:38:51,620
Depends on the details.

2270
01:38:51,620 --> 01:38:53,620
No, there's something special about

2271
01:38:53,620 --> 01:38:55,620
energy that grows at length.

2272
01:38:55,620 --> 01:38:59,620
As I said, what it really means in particle language

2273
01:38:59,620 --> 01:39:05,620
is that as you separate the constituents of the string,

2274
01:39:05,620 --> 01:39:08,620
as you pull it apart,

2275
01:39:10,620 --> 01:39:13,620
the energy of pulling it apart,

2276
01:39:13,620 --> 01:39:16,620
instead of just separating and making larger distances,

2277
01:39:16,620 --> 01:39:19,620
makes more particles.

2278
01:39:19,620 --> 01:39:22,120
So that the density of them

2279
01:39:22,120 --> 01:39:24,620
along the string always stays the same.

2280
01:39:24,620 --> 01:39:28,620
That's the character of these kind of strings.

2281
01:39:28,620 --> 01:39:31,620
And the other way to think about it

2282
01:39:31,620 --> 01:39:34,620
is there are strings made up out of field,

2283
01:39:34,620 --> 01:39:38,620
where because field lines are not allowed to end,

2284
01:39:38,620 --> 01:39:40,620
field lines are not allowed to end,

2285
01:39:40,620 --> 01:39:43,620
as long as the field doesn't spread out this way,

2286
01:39:43,620 --> 01:39:47,620
it has to remain uniform in the other direction.

2287
01:39:47,620 --> 01:39:51,620
So it's a characteristic of flux lines.

2288
01:39:51,620 --> 01:39:54,620
Flux lines which are confined to a tube.

2289
01:39:54,620 --> 01:39:57,120
If you had any kind

2290
01:39:57,120 --> 01:39:59,620
of situation where an electric field

2291
01:39:59,620 --> 01:40:02,120
were confined and prevented from

2292
01:40:02,120 --> 01:40:04,620
spreading out in the perpendicular direction,

2293
01:40:04,620 --> 01:40:08,620
the energy per unit length of it would be constant.

2294
01:40:08,620 --> 01:40:09,620
Yeah.

2295
01:40:10,620 --> 01:40:13,120
What about the kind of

2296
01:40:13,120 --> 01:40:15,620
residual motion along the p-z direction?

2297
01:40:15,620 --> 01:40:16,620
Along the z?

2298
01:40:16,620 --> 01:40:18,620
Ah, that's a very good question.

2299
01:40:18,620 --> 01:40:19,620
Yeah.

2300
01:40:19,620 --> 01:40:23,620
Remarkably, the way string theory works

2301
01:40:23,620 --> 01:40:27,620
is there are not independent degrees of freedom

2302
01:40:27,620 --> 01:40:29,620
for motion along the other direction.

2303
01:40:29,620 --> 01:40:32,620
This is a remarkable and strange fact

2304
01:40:32,620 --> 01:40:35,120
that in string theory you do

2305
01:40:35,120 --> 01:40:37,620
not include directly degrees of freedom

2306
01:40:37,620 --> 01:40:40,620
for the motion of the string along the direction

2307
01:40:40,620 --> 01:40:43,620
of the boost here.

2308
01:40:43,620 --> 01:40:45,120
It is thought that that's connected

2309
01:40:45,120 --> 01:40:46,620
with something called the holographic principle,

2310
01:40:46,620 --> 01:40:49,620
that really in a gravitating system you

2311
01:40:49,620 --> 01:40:52,620
need one less direct dimension to describe it,

2312
01:40:52,620 --> 01:40:54,620
but it's one of the

2313
01:40:54,620 --> 01:40:56,620
very remarkable features of string theory

2314
01:40:56,620 --> 01:40:59,620
that you don't describe the string in,

2315
01:40:59,620 --> 01:41:02,620
let's say in three-dimensional space,

2316
01:41:02,620 --> 01:41:04,620
in this limit you describe

2317
01:41:04,620 --> 01:41:06,620
it only by the two-dimensional motion,

2318
01:41:06,620 --> 01:41:09,620
and yet, as we will see,

2319
01:41:09,620 --> 01:41:14,620
it's consistent with Lorentz invariance.

2320
01:41:14,620 --> 01:41:15,620
Yeah.

2321
01:41:15,620 --> 01:41:17,620
How many data points do

2322
01:41:17,620 --> 01:41:19,620
we have on the Regiflots now?

2323
01:41:19,620 --> 01:41:21,620
Five or ten or?

2324
01:41:21,620 --> 01:41:24,620
I don't know what the maximum number is now.

2325
01:41:24,620 --> 01:41:26,620
Seven, something like that.

2326
01:41:26,620 --> 01:41:28,620
It's not endless,

2327
01:41:28,620 --> 01:41:32,620
but it doesn't give any evidence of giving out.

2328
01:41:32,620 --> 01:41:35,620
I'll talk about it another time,

2329
01:41:35,620 --> 01:41:37,620
but the evidence for that.

2330
01:41:37,620 --> 01:41:38,620
But remember,

2331
01:41:38,620 --> 01:41:40,620
that we're not really interested in hadrons.

2332
01:41:40,620 --> 01:41:43,620
I was just giving you a historical perspective

2333
01:41:43,620 --> 01:41:50,620
of where the whole thing came from.

2334
01:41:50,620 --> 01:41:54,620
But now we want to study this mathematical theory

2335
01:41:54,620 --> 01:41:57,620
and not insist that it looks like hadrons,

2336
01:41:57,620 --> 01:41:59,620
but just ask what it does look like.

2337
01:41:59,620 --> 01:42:00,620
And what we'll find out is

2338
01:42:00,620 --> 01:42:01,620
that it looks more like gravity

2339
01:42:01,620 --> 01:42:04,620
than it does hadrons.

2340
01:42:04,620 --> 01:42:07,620
Well, what if it was a electron?

2341
01:42:08,620 --> 01:42:10,620
What if it was something that is...

2342
01:42:10,620 --> 01:42:12,620
What if what was an electron?

2343
01:42:12,620 --> 01:42:15,120
Well, the idea that we

2344
01:42:15,120 --> 01:42:17,620
had some kind of spatial element

2345
01:42:17,620 --> 01:42:20,620
of the particle, the compositeness of the particle,

2346
01:42:20,620 --> 01:42:23,620
for a particle that doesn't seem to be composite...

2347
01:42:23,620 --> 01:42:25,620
Well, okay, let's be...

2348
01:42:25,620 --> 01:42:28,620
All right, so the question is...

2349
01:42:28,620 --> 01:42:31,620
can be expressed in two different ways.

2350
01:42:31,620 --> 01:42:33,620
Let's see.

2351
01:42:36,620 --> 01:42:37,620
It can be expressed...

2352
01:42:37,620 --> 01:42:39,620
or the answer to your question can be expressed

2353
01:42:39,620 --> 01:42:41,620
in terms of the smallness of the particle

2354
01:42:41,620 --> 01:42:44,620
or in terms of the energy that it takes

2355
01:42:44,620 --> 01:42:46,620
to increase the particle by one unit.

2356
01:42:46,620 --> 01:42:48,620
All right, so let's...

2357
01:42:48,620 --> 01:42:50,620
Do you remember the formula for the energy

2358
01:42:50,620 --> 01:42:52,620
of a rotating system as

2359
01:42:52,620 --> 01:42:54,620
a function of its angular momentum?

2360
01:42:54,620 --> 01:42:57,620
L squared, that's the angular momentum,

2361
01:42:57,620 --> 01:42:59,620
divided by two times something.

2362
01:42:59,620 --> 01:43:01,620
Remember what it is?

2363
01:43:01,620 --> 01:43:03,620
Moment of inertia.

2364
01:43:03,620 --> 01:43:06,620
And what's the moment of inertia related to?

2365
01:43:07,620 --> 01:43:10,620
The mass and the square

2366
01:43:10,620 --> 01:43:13,620
of the size of the system.

2367
01:43:13,620 --> 01:43:14,620
Right?

2368
01:43:14,620 --> 01:43:18,620
M R squared, not M squared, R squared.

2369
01:43:18,620 --> 01:43:20,620
M R squared.

2370
01:43:20,620 --> 01:43:23,620
But the point is that for a given mass,

2371
01:43:23,620 --> 01:43:26,620
the moment of inertia gets smaller and smaller

2372
01:43:26,620 --> 01:43:28,620
as the system gets...

2373
01:43:28,620 --> 01:43:32,620
Sorry, yes, the moment of inertia gets very small

2374
01:43:32,620 --> 01:43:34,620
when the system is very small.

2375
01:43:34,620 --> 01:43:35,620
Now, what is L?

2376
01:43:35,620 --> 01:43:36,620
L is angular momentum.

2377
01:43:37,620 --> 01:43:39,620
And it comes in quanta.

2378
01:43:39,620 --> 01:43:43,620
So this is proportional to N squared,

2379
01:43:43,620 --> 01:43:46,620
H bar squared, or something like that.

2380
01:43:46,620 --> 01:43:48,120
And now you can ask,

2381
01:43:48,120 --> 01:43:49,620
how much energy does it take

2382
01:43:49,620 --> 01:43:52,620
to go from N equals zero to N equals one?

2383
01:43:52,620 --> 01:43:56,620
N equals zero, the energy...

2384
01:43:56,620 --> 01:43:58,620
It might be a little bit of energy,

2385
01:43:58,620 --> 01:44:01,620
but the energy, this piece of the energy is zero.

2386
01:44:01,620 --> 01:44:04,620
The first excited state would have an energy

2387
01:44:04,620 --> 01:44:06,620
H bar squared over two,

2388
01:44:06,620 --> 01:44:09,620
one divided by the moment of inertia.

2389
01:44:09,620 --> 01:44:12,620
And if the object is very, very small,

2390
01:44:12,620 --> 01:44:15,620
the moment of inertia is very large.

2391
01:44:15,620 --> 01:44:17,620
No.

2392
01:44:17,620 --> 01:44:20,620
One over the moment of inertia is very large.

2393
01:44:20,620 --> 01:44:22,620
So the excitation energy,

2394
01:44:22,620 --> 01:44:27,620
the energy that it takes to increase the angular momentum

2395
01:44:27,620 --> 01:44:30,620
by one unit becomes very, very big

2396
01:44:30,620 --> 01:44:32,620
if the object is small.

2397
01:44:32,620 --> 01:44:34,620
Well, hadrons are big objects.

2398
01:44:34,620 --> 01:44:36,620
They have small moments of inertia

2399
01:44:36,620 --> 01:44:39,620
on the scale of quantum gravity.

2400
01:44:39,620 --> 01:44:41,620
Hadrons are just enormous.

2401
01:44:41,620 --> 01:44:45,620
I mean, they're, you know, they're big blobs.

2402
01:44:45,620 --> 01:44:48,620
They have large moments of inertia.

2403
01:44:48,620 --> 01:44:51,620
The energy taken to excite one is not very big.

2404
01:44:51,620 --> 01:44:54,620
Electrons are known to be much smaller.

2405
01:44:54,620 --> 01:44:57,620
The expectation is that they're exceedingly small,

2406
01:44:57,620 --> 01:45:01,620
maybe 10 to the 16th times smaller than a proton.

2407
01:45:01,620 --> 01:45:04,620
You square their radius to get the moment of inertia,

2408
01:45:04,620 --> 01:45:06,620
so that could mean 10 to

2409
01:45:06,620 --> 01:45:08,620
the 32 times smaller moment of inertia,

2410
01:45:08,620 --> 01:45:11,620
and that means that the energy of excitation

2411
01:45:11,620 --> 01:45:13,620
would be 10 to the 32 times bigger.

2412
01:45:13,620 --> 01:45:16,620
Well, maybe that's probably too much.

2413
01:45:16,620 --> 01:45:19,620
So if electrons have excited states,

2414
01:45:19,620 --> 01:45:21,620
because they're so small,

2415
01:45:21,620 --> 01:45:23,620
if they have rotational excitations,

2416
01:45:23,620 --> 01:45:26,620
those rotational excitations,

2417
01:45:26,620 --> 01:45:30,620
well, I think I lost my true Frouchy plot,

2418
01:45:30,620 --> 01:45:34,620
but the mass necessary to increase the angular momentum

2419
01:45:34,620 --> 01:45:37,620
by one unit would be way off on the,

2420
01:45:37,620 --> 01:45:40,620
no, that end of the plot.

2421
01:45:40,620 --> 01:45:42,620
Just too much, it just takes

2422
01:45:42,620 --> 01:45:44,620
too much energy to spin it up.

2423
01:45:44,620 --> 01:45:46,620
When I say too much, I

2424
01:45:46,620 --> 01:45:48,620
mean too much compared to the energies

2425
01:45:48,620 --> 01:45:51,620
that are available in particle collisions.

2426
01:45:51,620 --> 01:45:52,620
Okay?

2427
01:45:52,620 --> 01:45:55,120
So the energy needed to

2428
01:45:55,120 --> 01:45:57,620
excite a hadron by one unit

2429
01:45:57,620 --> 01:46:02,620
is less, is roughly of order of GeV.

2430
01:46:02,620 --> 01:46:04,620
You collide particles at a distance

2431
01:46:04,620 --> 01:46:06,620
of GeV or whatever it is,

2432
01:46:06,620 --> 01:46:08,620
you see these excitations.

2433
01:46:08,620 --> 01:46:12,620
The energy needed to spin up an electron

2434
01:46:12,620 --> 01:46:14,620
